<LegalPage title="Accessibility statement" description="CNVRT’s approach to website accessibility, known limitations and contact route for access problems.">
  <p class="legal-page__summary">CNVRT wants this website to be usable by as many people as reasonably possible. Our target is the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines, WCAG 2.2, at level AA.</p>

  <h2>1. What you should be able to do</h2>
  <p>The website is designed so that visitors can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>zoom and resize text without losing core content or functionality;</li>
    <li>navigate interactive controls using a keyboard;</li>
    <li>see a visible focus indicator;</li>
    <li>use labelled forms with announced validation and status messages;</li>
    <li>understand pages through semantic headings, landmarks and link text;</li>
    <li>pause or avoid non-essential motion through reduced-motion preferences; and</li>
    <li>use the site across common phone, tablet and desktop sizes without horizontal page scrolling.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Measures taken</h2>
  <p>Accessibility is considered during design and development rather than added only at the end. Measures include semantic HTML, keyboard-operable controls, alternative text for meaningful images, responsive layouts, colour-contrast review, reduced-motion support and visible form feedback.</p>

  <h2>3. Current status and limitations</h2>
  <p>Core routes have been reviewed across representative screen sizes and keyboard interactions. The site has not yet received an independent accessibility audit or a complete assistive-technology test. We do not currently know of a specific issue that prevents access to the principal content or enquiry routes, but further testing may identify improvements.</p>
  <p>Third-party services linked from the site are controlled by their providers and may not meet the same standard. We will record any confirmed material limitation here together with the planned resolution.</p>

  <h2>4. Requesting help or an alternative format</h2>
  <p>If you cannot access information, complete a form or use a feature, email <a href="mailto:hello@cnvrtdigital.co.uk">hello@cnvrtdigital.co.uk</a>. Include the page address, what you were trying to do and, if you are comfortable sharing it, the browser or assistive technology being used.</p>
  <p>We can provide reasonable alternative formats or another enquiry route where practicable. We aim to acknowledge accessibility reports within five working days.</p>

  <h2>5. Review</h2>
  <p>This statement is reviewed when a material feature, platform integration or design system changes, and after the final pre-launch accessibility audit.</p>
</LegalPage>
